# BioGate Project Context
# Drop this file in your repo root as .cursorrules

## What BioGate Is
AI-native BIOSECURE compliance platform. Automates supply chain auditing for biotech companies under the BIOSECURE Act (NDAA Section 851, signed Dec 2025).

## Existing Codebase (Week 5 complete)
- FastAPI backend with CSV upload endpoint
- Supabase PostgreSQL: tables = organizations, audits, vendors, watchlist_entities, watchlist_snapshots
- RapidFuzz fuzzy matching with configurable thresholds
- Claude API vendor normalization (normalized_name, country_hint, parent_company_hint, equipment_type_hint)
- Parent company resolution graph for BCC subsidiaries
- GitHub Actions daily watchlist refresh
- Manual override system with audit trail
- CLI: python run_audit.py --input vendors.csv --output report.json
- JSON risk report output

## Key Files
- backend/normalize.py — Claude API normalization (normalize_vendors_batch)
- backend/matching.py — RapidFuzz matching engine
- run_audit.py — CLI entry point
- Watchlists: BIS Entity List, OFAC SDN, UFLPA (~22K entities, ~60K names)

## Current Sprint: Multi-Format Document Ingestion
Building a universal ingestion engine at backend/ingestion/ that accepts CSV, Excel, PDF, images, email, and Word docs. All handlers produce ExtractedVendor records that feed into the existing matching pipeline.
